Pokemon.entry: It prepares for evolution using the energy it stored while it was a Wurmple.n It keeps watch over the surroundings with its two eyes.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shed Skin

Pokemon.name: Beautifly
Pokemon.entry: Its colorfully patterned wings are its most prominent feature. It files through flower-covered fields collecting pollen. It attacks ferociously when angered.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swarm | Hidden: Rivalry

Pokemon.name: Cascoon
Pokemon.entry: To avoid detection by its enemies, it hides motionlessly beneath large leaves and in the gaps of branches. It also attaches dead leaves to its body for camouflage.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shed Skin

Pokemon.name: Dustox
Pokemon.entry: It is a nocturnal Pokemon that files from fields and mountains to the attraction of streetlihts at night. It looses highly toxic powder from its wings.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shield Dust | Hidden: Compound Eyes

Pokemon.name: Lotad
Pokemon.entry: This Pokemon lives in ponds with clean water. It is known to ferry small Pokemon acrosss ponds by carrying them on the broad leaf on its head.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Rain Dish | Hidden: Own Tempo

Pokemon.name: Lombre
Pokemon.entry: In the evening, it takes great delight in popping out rivers and startling people. It feeds on aquatic moss that grows on rocks in the riverbed.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Rain Dish | Hidden: Own Tempo

Pokemon.name: Ludicolo
Pokemon.entry: When it hears festive music, all the cells in its body become stimulated, and it begins moving in rhythm. It does not quail even when it faces a tough opponent.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Rain Dish | Hidden: Own Tempo

Pokemon.name: Seedot
Pokemon.entry: It hangs off branches and absorbs nutrients. When it finishes eating, its body becomes so heavy that it drops to the ground with a thump.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Early Bird | Hidden: Pickpocket

Pokemon.name: Nuzleaf
Pokemon.entry: A forest-dwelling Pokemon that is skilled at climbing trees. Its long and pointed nose is its weak point. It loses power if the nose is gripped.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Early Bird | Hidden: Pickpocket

Pokemon.name: Shiftry
Pokemon.entry: It is said to arrive on chilly, wintry winds. Feared from long ago as the guardian of forests, this Pokemon lives in a deep forest where people do not venture.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Early Bird | Hidden: Pickpocket

Pokemon.name: Tailow
Pokemon.entry: Although it is small, it is very courageous. It will take on a larger Skarmory on an equal footing. However, its will weakens if it becomes hungry.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Guts | Hidden: Scrappy

Pokemon.name: Swellow
Pokemon.entry: A Swellow dives upon prey from far above. It never misses its targets. It takes to skies in search of lands with a warm climate.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Guts | Hidden: Scrappy

Pokemon.name: Wingull
Pokemon.entry: It makes its nest on a sheer cliff at the edge of the sea. It has trouble keeping its wings flapping in flight. Instead, it soars on updrafts.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Keen Eye, Hydration | Hidden: Rain Dish

Pokemon.name: Pelipper
Pokemon.entry: It skims the tops of waves as it flies. When it spots prey, it uses its large beak to scoop up the victim with water. It protects its eggs in its beak.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Keen Eye, Drizzle | Hidden: Rain Dish

Pokemon.name: Ralts
Pokemon.entry: A Ralts has the power to sense the emotions of people and Pokemon with the horns on its head. It takes cover if it senses any hostility.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Synchronize, Trace | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Kirlia
Pokemon.entry: A Kirlia has the psychic power to create a rip i the dimensions and see into the future. It said to dance with pleasure on sunny mornings.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Synchronize, Trace | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Gardevoir
Pokemon.entry: It apparently does not feel the pull of gravity because it supports itself with psychic power. It will give its life to protect its Trainer.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Synchronize, Trace | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Surskit
Pokemon.entry: They gather on puddles after eveningn downpours, gliding across the surface of water as if sliding. it secretes honey with a sweet aroma from its head.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim | Hidden: Rain Dish

Pokemon.name: Masquerain
Pokemon.entry: It intimidates foes with the large eyelike patterns on its antennae. Because it can't fly if its wings get wet, it shelters itself from rain under large trees and eaves.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate | Hidden: Unnerve

Pokemon.name: Shroomish
Pokemon.entry: It loves to eat damp, composted soil in forests. If you enter a forest after a long rain, you can see many Shroomish feasting on compsoted soil.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Effect Spore, Poison heal | Hidden: Quick Feet

Pokemon.name: Breloom
Pokemon.entry: It scatters spores from holes in the cap on its head. It loves warm andn humid climates. It feeds on trees and plants in fields and forests.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Effect Spore, Poison Heal | Hidden: Technician

Pokemon.name: Slakoth
Pokemon.entry: It sleeps virtually all day and night long. It doesn't change its nest its entire life, but it sometimes travels great distances by swimming in riivers.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Truant

Pokemon.name: Vigoroth
Pokemon.entry: It can't keep still because its blood boils with energy. It runs through the fields and mountains all day to calm itself. If it doesn't it can't sleep at night.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Vital Spirit

Pokemon.name: Slaking
Pokemon.entry: Hordes of Slaking lives, rings of over a yard in diameter appear in grassy fields. They wait around patientlyy for ripened fruits to fall out of the trees.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Truant

Pokemon.name: Nincada
Pokemon.entry: It makes its nest at the roots of a mighty tree. Using its whiskerlike antennae, it probes its surroundings in the pitch-black dakness of soil.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Compound Eyes | Hidden: Run Away

Pokemon.name: Ninjask
Pokemon.entry: Because it darts about vigorously at high speed, it is very difficult to see. Hearing its distinctive cries for too long induces a headache.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Speed Boost | Hidden: Infiltrator

Pokemon.name: Shedinja
Pokemon.entry: A peculiar Pokemon that floats in air even though its wings remain completely still. The inside of its body is hollow and utterly dark.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Wonder Guard

Pokemon.name: Whismur
Pokemon.entry: Its cries equal a jet plane in volume. It inhales through its ear canals. Because of this system, it can cry continually without having to catch its breath.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Soundproof | Hidden: Rattled

Pokemon.name: Loudred
Pokemon.entry: It positions the round speakers on its head to assail foes with ultrasonic waves at massive volumel. It builds power by stomping the ground
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Soundproof | Hidden: Scrappy

Pokemon.name: Exploud
Pokemon.entry: It has sound-generating organs all over its boyd. It communicats with others by adjusting the tone and volume of the cries it emits
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Soundproof | Hidden: Scrappy

Pokemon.name: Makuhita
Pokemon.entry: It loves to toughen up its body above all else. If you hear quaking rumbles in a cave, it is the sound of Makuhita undertaking strenous training.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Guts | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Hariyama
Pokemon.entry: It has the habit of challenging others without hesitation to tests of strength. It's been known to stand on train tracks and stop trains using forearm thrusts.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Guts | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Azurill
Pokemon.entry: Its tail, which is packed with nutrition, is very bouncy like a rubber ball. On sunny days they gather at the edge of water and splash about for fun.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Huge Power | Hidden: Sap Sipper

Pokemon.name: Nosepass
Pokemon.entry: Its body emits a powerful magnetism. It feeds on prey that is pulled in by the force. Its magnetism is stronger in cold seasons.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Magnet Pull | Hidden: Sand Force

Pokemon.name: Skitty
Pokemon.entry: A Skitty's adorably cute behavior makes it highly popular. In battle, it makes its tail puff out. It threatens foes with a sharp growl.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Cute Charm, Normalize | Hidden: Wonder Skin

Pokemon.name: Delcatty
Pokemon.entry: Rather than keeping a permanent lair, it habitually seeks comfortable spots andn sleeps there. It is nocturnal and becomes active at dusk.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Cute Charm, Normalize | Hidden: Wonder Skin

Pokemon.name: Sableye
Pokemon.entry: It digs branching holes in caves using its sharp claws in search of food - raw gems. A Sableye lurks in darkness and is seen only rarely.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Keen Eye, Stall | Hidden: Prankster

Pokemon.name: Mawile
Pokemon.entry: Its giant jaws are actually steel horns that transformed. It fools foes into complacency with its adorable gestures, then chomps them with its huge jaws.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hyper Cutter, Intimidate | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Aron
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that is clad in steel armor. A new suit of armor is made when it evolves. The old, discarded armor is salvaged as metal for making ironh products.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Rock Head | Hidden: Heavy Metal

Pokemon.name: Lairon
Pokemon.entry: When two Lairon meet in the wild, they fight for territory by bashing into each other with their steel bodies. The sound of their collision carries for miles.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Rock Head | Hidden: Heavy Metal

Pokemon.name: Aggron
Pokemon.entry: Its iron horns grow longer a little at a time. They are used to determine the Aggron's age. The gouges in its armor are worn with pride as mementos from battles.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Rock Head | Hidden: Heavy Metal

Pokemon.name: Meditite
Pokemon.entry: It continually mediates for hours every day. As a result of rigorous and dedicated yoga training, it has tempered its spiritual power so much it can fly.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Pure Power | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Medicham
Pokemon.entry: Through crushingly harsh yoga training, it gained the power to foretell its foe's actions. It battles with elegant, dance-like movement.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Pure Power | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Electrike
Pokemon.entry: It generates electricity using friciton from the atmosphere. In seasons with especially arid air, its entire body blazes with violent showers of sparks.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Static, Lightning | Hidden: Minus

Pokemon.name: Manetric
Pokemon.entry: Because lightning falls in their vicinities, Manectric were thought to have been born from lightning. In battle, they create thunderclouds.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Static, Lightning | Hidden: Minus

Pokemon.name: Plusle
Pokemon.entry: It has the trait of cheering on its fellow Pokemon. By shorting out the electricity it releases from its paws, it creates pom-poms for cheering.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Plus | Hidden: Lightning Rod

Pokemon.name: Minun
Pokemon.entry: At a meeting of Pokemon academics, it was announced the simultaneous exposure to electricity from a Plusle and Minun will promote circulation and boost vitality.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Minus | Hidden: Volt Absorb

Pokemon.name: Volbeat
Pokemon.entry: With their tailights lit, Volbeat fly in a swarm, drawing geometric designs in the night sky. They move their nests if their pond water becomes dirty.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Illuminate, Swarm | Hidden: Prankster

Pokemon.name: Illumise
Pokemon.entry: A nocturnal Pokemon that becomes active upon nightfall. It leads a Volbeat swarms to draw patterns in the night sky. Over 200 different patterns have been confirmed.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Oblivious, Tinted Lens | Hidden: Prankster

Pokemon.name: Roselia
Pokemon.entry: A Roselia that drinks nutritionally rich springwater blooms with lovely flowers. The fragrance of its flowers has the effect of making its foes careless.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Natural Cure, Poison Point | Hidden: Leaf Guard

Pokemon.name: Gulpin
Pokemon.entry: This Pokemon's stomach fluid can even digest scrap iron. In one gulp, it can swallow something that is as large as itself.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Liquid Ooze, Sticky Hold | Hidden: Gluttony

Pokemon.name: Swalot
Pokemon.entry: Its powerful stomach acid is capable of digesting almost anything. The one thing in the whole world a Swalot can't digest is its own stomach.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Liquid Ooze, Sticky Hold | Hidden: Gluttony

Pokemon.name: Carvanha
Pokemon.entry: Carvanha attack ships in swarms, making them sink. Although it is said to be a very vicious Pokemon, it timidly flees as soon as it finds itself alone.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rough Skin | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Sharpedo
Pokemon.entry: The vicious and sly gangster of the sea. Its skin is specially textured to minimize drag in water. Its speed tops out at over 75 mph.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rough Skin | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Wailmer
Pokemon.entry: While this Pokemon usually lives in the sea, it can survive on land, although not too long. It loses vitality if its body becomes dried out.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Water Veil, Oblivious | Hidden: Pressure

Pokemon.name: Wailord
Pokemon.entry: It breathes through nostrils that it raises avoe the sea. By inhaling to its maximum capacity, a Wailord can dive close to 10,000 feet beneath the waves.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Water Veil, Oblivious | Hidden: Pressure

Pokemon.name: Numel
Pokemon.entry: A Numel stores boiling magma in the hump on its back. It is a hardy Pokemon that can transport a 220-pound load. It has served humans at work since long ago.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Oblivious, Simple | Hidden: Own Tempo

Pokemon.name: Camerupt
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that lives in the crater of a volcano. Every 10 years, the volcanoes on its back erupt violently. Research is under way on the cause of eruption.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Magma Armor, Solid Rock | Hidden: Anger Point

Pokemon.name: Torkoal
Pokemon.entry: It battles using enery it gets from burning coal. When lossing smoke from its nostrils, it lets off a sound that is similar to a locomotive's horn.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: White Smoke, Drought | Hidden: Shell Armor

Pokemon.name: Spoink
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that manipulates psychic power at will. It doesn't stop bouncing even when it is asleep. It loves eating mushrooms that grow underground.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Own Tempo | Hidden: Gluttony

Pokemon.name: Grumpig
Pokemon.entry: It stores power in the black pearls on its forehead. When it uses psychic power, it performs an odd dance step. Its style of dancing became hugely popular overseas.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Own Tempo | Hidden: Gluttony

Pokemon.name: Spinda
Pokemon.entry: It is distinguished by a pattern of spots that is always different. Its unsteady, tottering walk has the effect of fouling its foe's aim.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Own Tempo, Tangled Feet | Hidden: Contrary

Pokemon.name: Trapinch
Pokemon.entry: Its big jaws crunch through boulders. Because its head is so big, it has a hard time getting back upright if it tips over onto its back.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hyper Cutter, Arena Trap | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Vibrava
Pokemon.entry: It looses ultrasonic waves by rubbing its wings together. Since a Vibrava's wings are still in the process of growing, it can only fly short distances.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Flygon
Pokemon.entry: The flapping of its wings sounds like singing. To prevent detection by enemies, it hides itself by flapping up a cloud of desert sand.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Cacnea
Pokemon.entry: Cacnea live in deserts with virtually no rainfall. It battles by swining its thick, spiked arms. Once a year, a yellow flower blooms.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sand Veil | Hidden: Water Absorb

Pokemon.name: Cacturne
Pokemon.entry: After spending thousands of years in harsh deserts, its blood transformed into the same substances as sand. It is nocturnal, so it hunts at night.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sand Veil | Hidden: Water Absorb

Pokemon.name: Swablu
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that has wings like cottony clouds. After enduring winter, in which little food is available, Swablu flocks move closer to towns in the spring.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Natural Cure | Hidden: Cloud Nine

Pokemon.name: Altaria
Pokemon.entry: It hums in a beautiful soprano voice. It flies white clouds in the blue sky. It launches intensely hot fireballs from its mouth.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Natural Cure | Hidden: Cloud Nine

Pokemon.name: Zangoose
Pokemon.entry: When it battles, it stands on its hind legs and attacks with its sharply clawed forelegs. Its fur bristles if it encounters any Seviper.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Immunity | Hidden: Toxic Boost

Pokemon.name: Seviper
Pokemon.entry: Seviper and Zangoose are eternal rivals. It counters a Zangoose's dazzlig agility with its swordlike tail, which also oozes a horrible poison.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shed Skin | Hidden: Infiltrator

Pokemon.name: Lunatone
Pokemon.entry: It becomes very active on the night of a full moon. This Pokemon was first discovered 40 years ago at the site of a meteor strike.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Solrock
Pokemon.entry: Solar energy is the source of this Pokemon's power. On sunny days, groups of Solrock line up facing the sun and absorb its light.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Barboach
Pokemon.entry: Its body is covered with a slimy film. The film acts as a barrier to prevent germs in muddy water from entering the Barboach's body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Oblivious, Anticipation | Hidden: Hydration

Pokemon.name: Whiscash
Pokemon.entry: Mysteriously, it can foretell earthquakes. In the daytime, it sleeps mud at the bottom of a pond. When it awakens, it continually feeds throughout the night.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Oblivious, Anticipation | Hidden: Hydration

Pokemon.name: Corphish
Pokemon.entry: Once its grips prey with its large pincers, it will never let go, no matter what. It is as hardy Pokemon that can thrive in any environment.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hyper Cutter, Shell Armor | Hidden: Adaptability

Pokemon.name: Crawdaunt
Pokemon.entry: A brutish Pokemon that loves to battle. A veteran Crawdaunt that has prevailed in hundredsd of battles has giant pincers marked with countless scars.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hyper Cutter, Shell Armor | Hidden: Adaptability

Pokemon.name: Baltoy
Pokemon.entry: A Baltoy moves by spinning on its single foot. It has been depicted in murals adorning the walls of a once-bustling city in an ancient age.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Claydol
Pokemon.entry: A Claydol sleeps while hovering in midair. Its arms are seperate from its body. They are kept floating by the Pokemon's manipulation of psychic power.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Lileep
Pokemon.entry: It disguises itself as seaweed by making its tentacles sway. Unsuspecting prey that come too close are swallowed whole. It became extinct 100 million years ago.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Suction Cups | Hidden: Storm Drain

Pokemon.name: Cradily
Pokemon.entry: It drags its heavy body along the seafloor. It makes its nest in the shallows of warms seas. Cradily can be seen on beaches when the tide goes out.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Suction Cups | Hidden: Storm Drain

Pokemon.name: Anorith
Pokemon.entry: It was resurrected from a fossil using the power of science. It swims by undulating the eight wings at its sides. They were feet that adapted to life in the sea.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Battle Armor | Hidden: Swift Swim

Pokemon.name: Armaldo
Pokemon.entry: Armaldo usually lives on land. However, when it hunts for prey, it dives beneath the ocean. It swims around using its two large wings.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Battle Armor | Hidden: Swift Swim

Pokemon.name: Feebas
Pokemon.entry: Feebas live in ponds that are heavily infested with weeds. Because of its hopelessly shabby appearance, it seems as if few Trainers raise it.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Oblivious | Hidden: Adaptability

Pokemon.name: Milotic
Pokemon.entry: It is said to live at the bottom of large lakes. Considered to be the most beautiful of all Pokemon, it has ben depicted in paintings and statues.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Marvel Scale, Competitive | Hidden: Cute Charm

Pokemon.name: Castform
Pokemon.entry: It alters its form depending on the weather. Changes in the cliamte such as the temperature and humidity appears to affects its cellular structure.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Forecast

Pokemon.name: Kecleon
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that has the ability to alter its body colors to match its surroundings. A Kecleon reverts to its original colors if it is startled.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Color Change | Hidden: Protean

Pokemon.name: Shuppet
Pokemon.entry: This Pokmeon roams about deep in the night seeking such negative emotions as grudges and envy. It retreats to its nest when the sun begins to rise.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Insomnia, Frisk | Hidden: Cursed Body

Pokemon.name: Banette
Pokemon.entry: An abandoned plush doll became this Pokemon. They are said to live in garbage dumps and wander about in search of the children that threw them away.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Insomnia, Frisk | Hidden: Cursed Body

Pokemon.name: Duskull
Pokemon.entry: A glare from its single scarlet eye makes even burly grown-ups freeze in utter fear. It is a nocturnal Pokemon that roams about under the cloak of darkness.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate | Hidden: Frisk

Pokemon.name: Dusclops
Pokemon.entry: It is throught that its body is holllow with only spectral ball of fire burning inside. However, no one has been able to confirm this theory as fact.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Pressure | Hidden: Frisk

Pokemon.name: Tropius
Pokemon.entry: It flies by flapping its broad leaves. The bunch of fruit that grows around its neck is delciously sweet. In the spring, it scatters pollen from its neck.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Solar Power | Hidden: Harvest

Pokemon.name: Chimecho
Pokemon.entry: They fly about very actively when the hot season arrives. They communicate among themselves using seven different and distinguishing cries.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Absol
Pokemon.entry: It sharply senses even subtle changes in the sky and the land to predict natural disasters. It is a long-lived Pokemon that has a life-span of 100 years.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Pressure, Super Luck | Hidden: Justified

Pokemon.name: Wynaut
Pokemon.entry: A Wynaut loves to eat sweet fruits. It cleverly picks fruits using its earlike arms. They gather in fruit gardens, drawn by the fragrance.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shadow Tag | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Snorunt
Pokemon.entry: They tend to move about in groups of aroundn five Snorunt. In snowy regions, it is said that when they are seen late at night, snowfall will arrive by morning.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Inner Focus, Ice Body | Hidden: Moody

Pokemon.name: Glalie
Pokemon.entry: A Glalie has the power to instantaneously freeze moisture in the atmosphere. A dazzling cloud of diamondlike ice crystals forms around its body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Inner Focus, Ice Body | Hidden: Moody

Pokemon.name: Spheal
Pokemon.entry: Its is completely covered with plushy fur. As a result, it never feels the cold even when it is rolling about on ice floes or driving in the sea.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Ice Body | Hidden: Oblivious

Pokemon.name: Sealeo
Pokemon.entry: Sealeo live in herds on ice floes. Using its powerful flippers, it shatters ice. It dives into the sea to hunt prey five times a day.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Ice Body | Hidden: Oblivious

Pokemon.name: Walrein
Pokemon.entry: To protect its herd, the leader battles anything that invades its territory, even at the cost of its life. Its tusks may snap off in battle.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Ice Body | Hidden: Oblivious

Pokemon.name: Clamperl
Pokemon.entry: A Clamperl slams its shell closed on prey to prevent escape. The peral it creates upon evolution is said to be infused with a mysterious energy.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shell Armor | Hidden: Rattled

Pokemon.name: Huntail
Pokemon.entry: To withstandthe crushing pressure of water deep under the sea, its spine is very thick and sturdy. Its tail, which is shaped like a small fish, has eyes that light up.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim | Hidden: Water Veil

Pokemon.name: Gorebyss
Pokemon.entry: A Gorebyss siphons the body fluids of prey through its thin, tubular mouth. Its light pink body color turns vivid when it finishes feeding.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim | Hidden: Hydration

Pokemon.name: Relicanth
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that was once believed to have been extinct. The species has not changed its form for 100 million years. It walks on the seafloor using its pectoral fins.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Rock Head | Hidden: Sturdy

Pokemon.name: Luvdisc
Pokemon.entry: Luvdisc make the branches of Corsola their nests. There is a custom from long ago of giving a Luvdisc as a gift to express one's feelings of love.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim | Hidden: Hydration

Pokemon.name: Bagon
Pokemon.entry: Although it is small, this Pokemon is very powerful because its body is a bundle of muscles. It launches head-butts with its ironlike skull.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rock Head | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Shelgon
Pokemon.entry: It hardly eats while it awaits evolution. It becomes hardier by enduring hunger. Its shell peels off the isntant it begins to evolve.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rock Head | Hidden: Overcoat

Pokemon.name: Salamence
Pokemon.entry: After many long years, its cellular structure underwent a sudden mutation to grow wings. When angered, it loses all thought and rampages out of control.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate | Hidden: Moxie

Pokemon.name: Beldum
Pokemon.entry: When Beldum gather in a swarm, they move in perfect unison as if they were but one Pokemon. They communicate with each other using brain waves.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Light Metal

Pokemon.name: Metang
Pokemon.entry: The claws tipping its arms pack the destructive power to tear through thick iron sheets as if they were silk. It files at over 60 miles per hour.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Light Metal

Pokemon.name: Metagross
Pokemon.entry: Metagross has four brains that are joined by a complex neural network. As a result of integration, this Pokemon is smarter than a supercomputer.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Light Metal

Pokemon.name: Regirock
Pokemon.entry: A Pokemon that is made entirely of rocks and boulders. If parts of its body chip off in battle, Regirock repairs itself by adding new rocks.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Sturdy

Pokemon.name: Regice
Pokemon.entry: Its entire body is made of Antartic ice. After extensive studies, researchers believe the ice was formed during an ice age.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Ice Body

Pokemon.name: Registeel
Pokemon.entry: Its body is harder than any other kind of metal. The body metal is composed of a mysterious substace. Not only is it hard, it shrinks and stretches flexibly.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Clear Body | Hidden: Light Metal

Pokemon.name: Latias
Pokemon.entry: They make a small herd of only several members. They rarely make contact with people or other Pokemon. They disappear if they sense enemies.

Pokemon.name: Tranquill

Pokemon.name: Unfezant
Pokemon.entry: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.

Pokemon.name: Zebstrika

Pokemon.name: Boldore

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Weak Armor | Hidden: Sand Force

Pokemon.name: Gigalith
Pokemon.entry: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Sand Stream | Hidden: Sand Force

Pokemon.name: Woobat

Pokemon.name: Swoobat
Pokemon.entry: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Unaware, Klutz | Hidden: Simple

Pokemon.name: Drilbur
Pokemon.entry: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sand Rush, Sand Force | Hidden: Mold Breaker

Pokemon.name: Excadrill
Pokemon.entry: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sand Rush, Sand Force | Hidden: Mold Breaker

Pokemon.name: Audino
Pokemon.entry: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Healer, Regenerator | Hidden: Klutz

Pokemon.name: Timburr
Pokemon.entry: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Guts, Sheer Force | Hidden: Iron Fist

Pokemon.name: Gurdurr
Pokemon.entry: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Guts, Sheer Force | Hidden: Iron Fist

Pokemon.name: Conkeldurr
Pokemon.entry: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Guts, Sheer Force | Hidden: Iron Fist

Pokemon.name: Tympole
Pokemon.entry: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.

Pokemon.name: Palpitoad

Pokemon.name: Seismitoad
Pokemon.entry: By putting power into its bumps, it creates vibrations and increases the power of its punches.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swift Swim, Poison Touch | Hidden: Water Absorb

Pokemon.name: Throh

Pokemon.name: Sawk
Pokemon.entry: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Inner Focus | Hidden: Mold Breaker

Pokemon.name: Sewaddle

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swarm, Chlorophyll | Hidden: Overcoat

Pokemon.name: Swadloon

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Leaf Guard, Chlorophyll | Hidden: Overcoat

Pokemon.name: Leavanny

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swarm, Chlorophyll | Hidden: Overcoat

Pokemon.name: Venipede
Pokemon.entry: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey's location and state.

Pokemon.name: Whirlipede

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Poison Point, Swarm | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Scolipede
Pokemon.entry: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Poison Point, Swarm | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Cottonee
Pokemon.entry: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Prankster, Infiltrator | Hidden: Chlorophyll

Pokemon.name: Whimsicott
Pokemon.entry: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Prankster, Infiltrator | Hidden: Chlorophyll

Pokemon.name: Petilil
Pokemon.entry: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Own Tempo | Hidden: Leaf Guard

Pokemon.name: Lilligant
Pokemon.entry: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Own Tempo | Hidden: Leaf Guard

Pokemon.name: Basculin
Pokemon.entry: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

Pokemon.name: Sandile
Pokemon.entry: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Moxie | Hidden: Anger Point

Pokemon.name: Krokorok
Pokemon.entry: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Moxie | Hidden: Anger Point

Pokemon.name: Krookodile
Pokemon.entry: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Moxie | Hidden: Anger Point

Pokemon.name: Darumaka
Pokemon.entry: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100°F.

Pokemon.name: Darmanitan
Pokemon.entry: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

Pokemon.name: Maractus
Pokemon.entry: When it moves rhythmically, it makes a sound similar to maracas, making the surprised Pokémon flee.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Water Absorb, Chlorophyll | Hidden: Storm Drain

Pokemon.name: Dweeble
Pokemon.entry: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Shell Armor | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Crustle
Pokemon.entry: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sturdy, Shell Armor | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Scraggy
Pokemon.entry: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shed Skin, Moxie | Hidden: Intimidate

Pokemon.name: Scrafty
Pokemon.entry: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Shed Skin, Moxie | Hidden: Intimidate

Pokemon.name: Cofagrigus

Pokemon.name: Tirtouga

Pokemon.name: Carracosta

Pokemon.name: Archeops
Pokemon.entry: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Defeatist

Pokemon.name: Zorua

Pokemon.name: Zoroark

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Frisk, Competitive | Hidden: Shadow Tag

Pokemon.name: Galvantula

Pokemon.name: Ferroseed

Pokemon.name: Beheeyem

Pokemon.name: Litwick

Pokemon.name: Chandelure

Pokemon.name: Axew

Pokemon.name: Haxorus
Pokemon.entry: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rivalry, Mold Breaker | Hidden: Unnerve

Pokemon.name: Cubchoo

Pokemon.name: Beartic
Pokemon.entry: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Snow Cloak, Slush Rush | Hidden: Swift Swim

Pokemon.name: Cryogonal
Pokemon.entry: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148° F.

Pokemon.name: Shelmet
Pokemon.entry: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hydration, Shell Armor | Hidden: Overcoat

Pokemon.name: Accelgor
Pokemon.entry: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.

Pokemon.name: Stunfisk

Pokemon.name: Mienfoo

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Inner Focus, Regenerator | Hidden: Reckless

Pokemon.name: Mienshao

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Inner Focus, Regenerator | Hidden: Reckless

Pokemon.name: Druddigon

Pokemon.name: Golurk

Pokemon.name: Pawniard

Pokemon.name: Bisharp

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Defiant, Inner Focus | Hidden: Pressure

Pokemon.name: Buffalant

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Reckless, Sap Sipper | Hidden: Soundproof

Pokemon.name: Rufflet

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Keen Eye, Sheer Force | Hidden: Hustle

Pokemon.name: Braviary
Pokemon.entry: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Keen Eye, Sheer Force | Hidden: Defiant

Pokemon.name: Vullaby
Pokemon.entry: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Big Pecks, Overcoat | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Mandibuzz
Pokemon.entry: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Big Pecks, Overcoat | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Heatmor

Pokemon.name: Durant

Pokemon.name: Deino

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hustle

Pokemon.name: Zweilous
Pokemon.entry: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.

Pokemon.name: Hydreigon

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Levitate

Pokemon.name: Larvesta
Pokemon.entry: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Flame Body, | Hidden: Swarm

Pokemon.name: Volcarona
Pokemon.entry: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokémon from freezing.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Flame Body | Hidden: Swarm

Pokemon.name: Cobalion

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Justified

Pokemon.name: Terrakion
Pokemon.entry: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Justified

Pokemon.name: Virizion
Pokemon.entry: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Justified

Pokemon.name: Tornadus
Pokemon.entry: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Prankster | Hidden: Defiant

Pokemon.entry: "	As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked."
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Prankster | Hidden: Defiant

Pokemon.name: Reshiram
Pokemon.entry: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

Pokemon.name: Zekrom

Pokemon.abilities: Main: Teravolt

Pokemon.name: Meloetta

Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.

Pokemon.name: Enamorus
Pokemon.entry: When it flies to this land from across the sea, the bitter winter comes to an end. According to legend, this Pokemon's love gives rise to the budding of fresh life across Hisui
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Healer | Hidden: Contrary

Pokemon.name: Sprigatito
Pokemon.entry: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Overgrow | Hidden: Protean

Pokemon.name: Floragato
Pokemon.entry: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Overgrow | Hidden: Protean

Pokemon.name: Meowscarada
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Overgrow | Hidden: Protean

Pokemon.name: Fuecoco
Pokemon.entry: It lies on warm rocks and uses the heat absorbed by its square-shaped scales to create fire energy.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Blaze | Hidden: Unaware

Pokemon.name: Crocalor
Pokemon.entry: The combination of Crocalor’s fire energy and overflowing vitality has caused an egg-shaped fireball to appear on the Pokémon’s head.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Blaze | Hidden: Unaware

Pokemon.name: Skeledirge
Pokemon.entry: The fiery bird changes shape when Skeledirge sings. Rumor has it that the bird was born when the fireball on Skeledirge’s head gained a soul.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Blaze | Hidden: Unaware

Pokemon.name: Quaxly
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon migrated to Paldea from distant lands long ago. The gel secreted by its feathers repels water and grime.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Torrent | Hidden: Moxie

Pokemon.name: Quaxwell
Pokemon.entry: These Pokémon constantly run through shallow waters to train their legs, then compete with each other to see which of them kicks most gracefully.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Torrent | Hidden: Moxie

Pokemon.name: Quaquaval
Pokemon.entry: A single kick from a Quaquaval can send a truck rolling. This Pokémon uses its powerful legs to perform striking dances from far-off lands.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Torrent | Hidden: Moxie

Pokemon.name: Lechonk
Pokemon.entry: It searches for food all day. It possesses a keen sense of smell but doesn’t use it for anything other than foraging.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Aroma Veil, Gluttony | Hidden: Thick Fat

Pokemon.name: Oinkologne
Pokemon.entry: Oinkologne is proud of its fine, glossy skin. It emits a concentrated scent from the tip of its tail.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Aroma Veil, Gluttony | Hidden: Thick Fat

Pokemon.name: Tarountula
Pokemon.entry: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon’s natural enemy.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Insomnia | Hidden: Stakeout

Pokemon.name: Spidops
Pokemon.entry: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Insomnia | Hidden: Stakeout

Pokemon.name: Nymble
Pokemon.entry: It has its third set of legs folded up. When it’s in a tough spot, this Pokémon jumps over 30 feet using the strength of its legs.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swarm | Hidden: Tinted Lens

Pokemon.name: Lokix
Pokemon.entry: When it decides to fight all out, it stands on its previously folded legs to enter Showdown Mode. It neutralizes its enemies in short order.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Swarm | Hidden: Tinted Lens

Pokemon.name: Pawmi
Pokemon.entry: It has underdeveloped electric sacs on its cheeks. These sacs can produce electricity only if Pawmi rubs them furiously with the pads on its forepaws.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Static, Natural Cure | Hidden: Iron Fist

Pokemon.name: Pawmo
Pokemon.entry: When its group is attacked, Pawmo is the first to leap into battle, defeating enemies with a fighting technique that utilizes electric shocks.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Volt Absorb, Natural Cure | Hidden: Iron Fist

Pokemon.name: Pawmot
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon normally is slow to react, but once it enters battle, it will strike down its enemies with lightning-fast movements.
Pokemon.abilities: Main:  | Hidden:

Pokemon.name: Tandemaus
Pokemon.entry: Exhibiting great teamwork, they use their incisors to cut pieces out of any material that might be useful for a nest, then make off with them.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Run Away, Pickup | Hidden: Own Tempo

Pokemon.name: Maushold
Pokemon.entry: The two little ones just appeared one day. The group might be a family of related Pokémon, but nobody knows for sure
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Friend Guard, Cheek Pouch | Hidden: Technician

Pokemon.name: Fidough
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon is smooth and moist to the touch. Yeast in Fidough’s breath induces fermentation in the Pokémon’s vicinity.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Own Tempo | Hidden: Klutz

Pokemon.name: Dachsbun
Pokemon.entry: The pleasant aroma that emanates from this Pokémon’s body helps wheat grow, so Dachsbun has been treasured by farming villages.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Well-Baked Body | Hidden: Aroma Veil

Pokemon.name: Smoliv
Pokemon.entry: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Early Bird | Hidden: Harvest

Pokemon.name: Dolliv
Pokemon.entry: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Early Bird | Hidden: Harvest

Pokemon.name: Arboliva
Pokemon.entry: This calm Pokémon is very compassionate. It will share its delicious, nutrient-rich oil with weakened Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Seed Sower | Hidden: Harvest

Pokemon.name: Squawkabilly
Pokemon.entry: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Hustle | Hidden: Guts, Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Nacli
Pokemon.entry: It was born in a layer of rock salt deep under the earth. This species was particularly treasured in the old days, as they would share precious salt.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Purifying Salt, Sturdy | Hidden: Clear Body

Pokemon.name: Naclstack
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon dry cures its prey by spraying salt over them. The curing process steals away the water in the prey’s body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Purifying Salt, Sturdy | Hidden: Clear Body

Pokemon.name: Garganacl
Pokemon.entry: Garganacl will rub its fingertips together and sprinkle injured Pokémon with salt. Even severe wounds will promptly heal afterward.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Purifying Salt, Sturdy | Hidden: Clear Body

Pokemon.name: Charcadet
Pokemon.entry: Burnt charcoal came to life and became a Pokémon. Possessing a fiery fighting spirit, Charcadet will battle even tough opponents.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Flash Fire | Hidden: Flame Body

Pokemon.name: Armarouge
Pokemon.entry: Armarouge evolved through the use of a set of armor that belonged to a distinguished warrior. This Pokémon is incredibly loyal.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Flash Fire | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Ceruledge
Pokemon.entry: The fiery blades on its arms burn fiercely with the lingering resentment of a sword wielder who fell before accomplishing their goal.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Flash Fire | Hidden: Weak Armor

Pokemon.name: Tadbulb
Pokemon.entry: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Own Tempo, Static | Hidden: Damp

Pokemon.name: Bellibolt
Pokemon.entry: When this Pokémon expands and contracts its wobbly body, the belly-button dynamo in its stomach produces a huge amount of electricity.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Electromorphosis, Static | Hidden: Damp

Pokemon.name: Wattrel
Pokemon.entry: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Wind Power, Volt Absorb | Hidden: Competitive

Pokemon.name: Kilowatteral
Pokemon.entry: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Wind Power, Volt Absorb | Hidden: Competitive

Pokemon.name: Maschiff
Pokemon.entry: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff’s face.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Run Away | Hidden: Stakeout

Pokemon.name: Mabosstiff
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon can store energy in its large dewlap. Mabosstiff unleashes this energy all at once to blow away enemies.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Intimidate, Guard Dog | Hidden: Stakeout

Pokemon.name: Shroodle
Pokemon.entry: Though usually a mellow Pokémon, it will sink its sharp, poison-soaked front teeth into any that anger it, causing paralysis in the object of its ire.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Unburden, Pickpocket | Hidden: Prankster

Pokemon.name: Grafaiai
Pokemon.entry: The color of the poisonous saliva depends on what the Pokémon eats. Grafaiai covers its fingers in its saliva and draws patterns on trees in forests.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Unburden, Poison Touch | Hidden: Prankster

Pokemon.name: Bramblin
Pokemon.entry: A soul unable to move on to the afterlife was blown around by the wind until it got tangled up with dried grass and became a Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Wind Rider | Hidden: Infiltrator

Pokemon.name: Brambleghast
Pokemon.entry: It will open the branches of its head to envelop its prey. Once it absorbs all the life energy it needs, it expels the prey and discards it.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Wind Rider | Hidden: Infiltrator

Pokemon.name: Toedscool
Pokemon.entry: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mycelium Might

Pokemon.name: Toedscruel
Pokemon.entry: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mycelium Might

Pokemon.name: Klawf
Pokemon.entry: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can’t remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Anger Shell, Shell Armor | Hidden: Regenerator

Pokemon.name: Capsakid
Pokemon.entry: The more sunlight this Pokémon bathes in, the more spicy chemicals are produced by its body, and thus the spicier its moves become.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Insomnia | Hidden: Klutz

Pokemon.name: Scovillain
Pokemon.entry: The red head converts spicy chemicals into fire energy and blasts the surrounding area with a super spicy stream of flame.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Chlorophyll, Insomnia | Hidden: Moody

Pokemon.name: Rellor
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon creates a mud ball by mixing sand and dirt with psychic energy. It treasures its mud ball more than its own life.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Compound Eyes | Hidden: Shed Skin

Pokemon.name: Rabsca
Pokemon.entry: The body that supports the ball barely moves. Therefore, it is thought that the true body of this Pokémon is actually inside the ball.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Synchronize | Hidden: Telepathy

Pokemon.name: Flittle
Pokemon.entry: Flittle’s toes levitate about half an inch above the ground because of the psychic power emitted from the frills on the Pokémon’s belly.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Anticipation, Frisk | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Espathra
Pokemon.entry: It immobilizes opponents by bathing them in psychic power from its large eyes. Despite its appearance, it has a vicious temperament.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Opportunist, Frisk | Hidden: Speed Boost

Pokemon.name: Tinkatink
Pokemon.entry: It swings its handmade hammer around to protect itself, but the hammer is often stolen by Pokémon that eat metal.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mold Breaker, Own Tempo | Hidden: Pickpoket

Pokemon.name: Tinkabuff
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon will attack groups of Pawniard and Bisharp, gathering metal from them in order to create a large and sturdy hammer.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mold Breaker, Own Tempo | Hidden: Pickpoket

Pokemon.name: Tinkaton
Pokemon.entry: This intelligent Pokémon has a very daring disposition. It knocks rocks into the sky with its hammer, aiming for flying Corviknight.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mold Breaker, Own Tempo | Hidden: Pickpoket

Pokemon.name: Wiglett
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon can pick up the scent of a Veluza just over 65 feet away and will hide itself in the sand.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Gooey, Rattled | Hidden: Sand Veil

Pokemon.name: Wugtrio
Pokemon.entry: It has a vicious temperament, contrary to what its appearance may suggest. It wraps its long bodies around prey, then drags the prey into its den.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Gooey, Rattled | Hidden: Sand Veil

Pokemon.name: Bombirdier
Pokemon.entry: It gathers things up in an apron made from shed feathers added to the Pokémon’s chest feathers, then drops those things from high places for fun.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Big Pecks, Keen Eye | Hidden: Rocky Payload

Pokemon.name: Finizen
Pokemon.entry: It likes playing with others of its kind using the water ring on its tail. It uses ultrasonic waves to sense the emotions of other living creatures.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Water Veil

Pokemon.name: Palafin
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon changes its appearance if it hears its allies calling for help. Palafin will never show anybody its moment of transformation.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Zero to Hero

Pokemon.name: Varoom
Pokemon.entry: It is said that this Pokémon was born when an unknown poison Pokémon entered and inspirited an engine left at a scrap-processing factory.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Overcoat | Hidden: Slow Start

Pokemon.name: Revavroom
Pokemon.entry: It creates a gas out of poison and minerals from rocks. It then detonates the gas in its cylinders— now numbering eight—to generate energy.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Overcoat | Hidden: Filter

Pokemon.name: Cyclizar
Pokemon.entry: Apparently Cyclizar has been allowing people to ride on its back since ancient times. Depictions of this have been found in 10,000-year-old murals.
Pokemon.abilities: Main:  | Hidden:

Pokemon.name: Orthworm
Pokemon.entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will wield the tendrils on its body like fists and pelt the opponent with a storm of punches.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Earth Eater | Hidden: Sand Veil

Pokemon.name: Glimmet
Pokemon.entry: It absorbs nutrients from cave walls. The petals it wears are made of crystallized poison.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Toxic Debris | Hidden: Corrosion

Pokemon.name: Glimmora
Pokemon.entry: When this Pokémon detects danger, it will open up its crystalline petals and fire beams from its conical body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Toxic Debris | Hidden: Corrosion

Pokemon.name: Greavard
Pokemon.entry: It is said that a dog Pokémon that died in the wild without ever interacting with a human was reborn as this Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Pickup | Hidden: Fluffy

Pokemon.name: Houndstone
Pokemon.entry: Houndstone spends most of its time sleeping in graveyards. Among all the dog Pokémon, this one is most loyal to its master.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sand Rush | Hidden: Fluffy

Pokemon.name: Flamigo
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon apparently ties the base of its neck into a knot so that the energy stored in its belly does not escape from its beak.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Scrappy, Tangled Feet | Hidden: Costar

Pokemon.name: Cetoddle
Pokemon.entry: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Snow Cloak | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Cetitan
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon wanders around snowy, icy areas. It protects its body with powerful muscles and a thick layer of fat under its skin.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thick Fat, Slush Rush | Hidden: Sheer Force

Pokemon.name: Veluza
Pokemon.entry: When Veluza discards unnecessary flesh, its mind becomes honed and its psychic power increases. The spare flesh has a mild but delicious flavor.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Mold Breaker | Hidden: Sharpness

Pokemon.name: Dondozo
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon is a glutton, but it’s bad at getting food. It teams up with a Tatsugiri to catch prey.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Unaware, Oblivious | Hidden: Water Veil

Pokemon.name: Tatsugiri
Pokemon.entry: This is a small dragon Pokémon. It lives inside the mouth of Dondozo to protect itself from enemies on the outside.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Commander | Hidden: Storm Drain

Pokemon.name: Annihilape
Pokemon.entry: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Vital Spirit, Inner Focus | Hidden: Defiant

Pokemon.name: Clodsire
Pokemon.entry: When attacked, this Pokémon will retaliate by sticking thick spines out from its body. It’s a risky move that puts everything on the line.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Poison Point, Water Absorb | Hidden: Unaware

Pokemon.name: Fairgiraf
Pokemon.entry: Now that the brain waves from the head and tail are synced up, the psychic power of this Pokémon is 10 times stronger than Girafarig’s.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Cud Chew, Armor Tail | Hidden: Sap Sipper

Pokemon.name: Dudunsparce
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon uses its hard tail to make its nest by boring holes into bedrock deep underground. The nest can reach lengths of over six miles.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Serene Grace, Run Away | Hidden: Rattled

Pokemon.name: Kingambit
Pokemon.entry: Only a Bisharp that stands above all others in its vast army can evolve into Kingambit.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Defiant, Supreme Overlord | Hidden: Pressure

Pokemon.name: Great Tusk
Pokemon.entry: Sightings of this Pokémon have occurred in recent years. The name Great Tusk was taken from a creature listed in a certain book.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Scream Tail
Pokemon.entry: There has been only one reported sighting of this Pokémon. It resembles a mysterious creature depicted in an old expedition journal.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Brute Bonnet
Pokemon.entry: It is possible that the creature listed as Brute Bonnet in a certain book could actually be this Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Flutter Mane
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon has characteristics similar to those of Flutter Mane, a creature mentioned in a certain book.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Slither Wing
Pokemon.entry: This mysterious Pokémon has some similarities to a creature that an old book introduced as Slither Wing.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Sandy Shocks
Pokemon.entry: No records exist of this Pokémon being caught. Data is lacking, but the Pokémon’s traits match up with a creature shown in an expedition journal.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Iron Treads
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon closely resembles a scientific weapon that a paranormal magazine claimed was sent to this planet by aliens.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Iron Bundle
Pokemon.entry: Its shape is similar to a robot featured in a paranormal magazine article. The robot was said to have been created by an ancient civilization.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Iron Hands
Pokemon.entry: It is very similar to a cyborg covered exclusively by a paranormal magazine. The cyborg was said to be the modified form of a certain athlete.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Iron Jugulis
Pokemon.entry: It resembles a certain Pokémon introduced in a paranormal magazine, described as the offspring of a Hydreigon that fell in love with a robot.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Iron Moth
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon resembles an unknown object described in a paranormal magazine as a UFO sent to observe humanity.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Iron Thorns
Pokemon.entry: It has some similarities to a Pokémon introduced in a dubious magazine as a Tyranitar from one billion years into the future.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Frigibax
Pokemon.entry: Frigibax absorbs heat through its dorsal fin and converts the heat into ice energy. The higher the temperature, the more energy Frigibax stores.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thermal Exchange | Hidden: Ice Body

Pokemon.name: Arctibax
Pokemon.entry: Arctibax freezes the air around it, protecting its face with an ice mask and turning its dorsal fin into a blade of ice.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thermal Exchange | Hidden: Ice Body

Pokemon.name: Baxcalibur
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon blasts cryogenic air out from its mouth. This air can instantly freeze even liquid-hot lava.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Thermal Exchange | Hidden: Ice Body

Pokemon.name: Gimmighoul
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon was born inside a treasure chest about 1,500 years ago. It sucks the life-force out of scoundrels who try to steal the treasure.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Rattled | Hidden: Run Away

Pokemon.name: Gholdengo
Pokemon.entry: Its body seems to be made up of 1,000 coins. This Pokémon gets along well with others and is quick to make friends with anybody.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Good as Gold

Pokemon.name: Wo-Chien
Pokemon.entry: The grudge of a person punished for writing the king’s evil deeds upon wooden tablets has clad itself in dead leaves to become a Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Tablets of Ruin

Pokemon.name: Chien-Pao
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon can control 100 tons of fallen snow. It plays around innocently by leaping in and out of avalanches it has caused.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Sword of Ruin

Pokemon.name: Ting-Lu
Pokemon.entry: The fear poured into an ancient ritual vessel has clad itself in rocks and dirt to become a Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Vessel of Ruin

Pokemon.name: Chi-Yu
Pokemon.entry: It controls flames burning at over 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit. It casually swims through the sea of lava it creates by melting rock and sand.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Beads of Ruin

Pokemon.name: Roaring Moon
Pokemon.entry: It is possible that this is the creature listed as Roaring Moon in an expedition journal that still holds many mysteries.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Iron Valiant
Pokemon.entry: It has some similarities to a mad scientist’s invention covered in a paranormal magazine.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Koraidon
Pokemon.entry: This seems to be the Winged King mentioned in an old expedition journal. It was said to have split the land with its bare fists.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Orichalcum Pulse

Pokemon.name: Miraidon
Pokemon.entry: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hadron Engine

Pokemon.name: Walking Wake
Pokemon.entry: Ecology under research.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Protosynthesis

Pokemon.name: Iron Leaves
Pokemon.entry: Ecology under research.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Quark Drive

Pokemon.name: Dipplin
Pokemon.entry: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Supersweet Syrup | Gluttony Hidden: Sticky Hold

Pokemon.name: Poltchageist
Pokemon.entry: Supposedly, the regrets of a tea ceremony master who died before perfecting his craft lingered in some matcha and became a Pokémon.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hospitality | Hidden: Heatproof

Pokemon.name: Sinistcha
Pokemon.entry: It pretends to be tea, trying to fool people into drinking it so it can drain their life-force. Its ruse is generally unsuccessful.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Hospitality | Hidden: Heatproof

Pokemon.name: Okidogi
Pokemon.entry: After all its muscles were stimulated by the toxic chain around its neck, Okidogi transformed and gained a powerful physique.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Toxic Chain | Hidden: Guard Dog

Pokemon.name: Munkidori
Pokemon.entry: The chain is made from toxins that enhance capabilities. It stimulated Munkidori's brain and caused the Pokémon's psychic powers to bloom.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Toxic Chain | Hidden: Frisk

Pokemon.name: Fezandipiti
Pokemon.entry: Fezandipiti owes its beautiful looks and lovely voice to the toxic stimulants emanating from the chain wrapped around its body.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Toxic Chain | Hidden: Technician

Pokemon.name: Ogerpon
Pokemon.entry: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.
Pokemon.abilities: Main: Defiant | Hidden: Embody Aspect
